spans.text: high on yonder hanging Rock they feed : And here below , the banky Shore along , Your Heifers graze : And I to hear your song Disposed
My Goats , secure from Harm , small Tendance
others meanly stake upon their Skill , Or Kid , or Lamb , or Goat , or what they will
All varnished , and with brazen Ringlets
The Ground bestrewed with Fruits off every Tree , And stormy Winds are heard
Winter near , Nor trust too far to the declining Year
the Shepherd's Friend : Eternal Blessings on his Shade attend
my Love in secret all repaid
a sidelong Eye : Then swift beneath the crystal Wave she tried Her tempting Form , but all in vain , to hide
swift beneath the crystal Wave she tried Her tempting Form
beneath the crystal Wave she tried Her tempting Form
to refrain my madding Mind , Nor Sheep nor Pasture worth my Care I find
my fond Heart the racking Pains of Love
Who sung through all the Seasons of the Year
All varnished , and with brazen Ringlets
